commitResults.messageTitle: Started the individual project by renaming ChatBot, and updating the Logo to reflect the change. Included external tool used in generating logo.
Added greet method that displays greeting message, separated logo into its own method to have a tidier main method.
Added greet method that displays greeting message, separated logo into its own method to have a tidier main method.
Added goodbye message to its own method, added a loop that prompts user input and echoes message until bye prompt.
Added goodbye message to its own method, added a loop that prompts user input and echoes message until bye prompt. Added personality.

Added adding and listing functionality using dynamic size ArrayList. Tweaked some of the display messages.
Added adding and listing functionality using dynamic size ArrayList. Tweaked some of the display messages.
Added marking as done/undone feature, created Task class with getter/setter methods, parsed user input to extract command and argument (index), changed if-else to switch to handle more cases,

Added support for 3 types of tasks, backward compatibility for tasks with no special type, parsed user input using string builder to separate command, task name and additional time info. Implemented toString methods across superclass and subclasses.
Added Automated Text UI Testing, with input.txt loaded with most typical user input used for testing, and EXPECTED.TXT updated with output from current correct behavior.

Added exception handling to handle empty, invalid user inputs, incorrect usage of commands, redundant arguments. Added help command with correct usage for user-friendliness. Updated text ui tester. Minor visual tweaks.

Added support for delete function (I had been using ArrayList from the start), updated text ui testing

Implemented switch with enum, as commands have a small set of possible values. Also, observed benefit of automated text ui testing as no change in behavior was expected from this change, and it allowed for easily confirming it.
